---
Source:
  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  ID: 50ae0a98-5702-40cb-8c11-4c6297aa457a
  Translator: Burton Watson
By: Zhuangzi
Locus:
  Chapter: 2
  Paragraph: 51
Title: Discussion On Making All Things Equal
---
Shadow said, "Do I have to wait for something before I can be like
this? Does what I wait for also have to wait for something before it
can be like this? Am I waiting for the scales of a snake or the wings
of a cicada? How do I know why it is so? How do I know why it isn't
so?"
